The Caleshan Valkyrie wrote:Now I'm curious what difference the hyphen makes... so there were a bunch of blonde and blue-eyed vagabonds tramping about?

/stillme

Nah, the Nazis appropriated Aryan to mean Germanic (or more specifically Germans made to look like Nords) because the prevailing theory at the time was that the presence of symbols like the swastika (as a symbol of peace) in archeological sites across Eurasia meant that there had been an "Aryan" empire across the continent at some point in the ancient past, which they used to justify their war and to do their whole ethnonationalism thing. The actual Aryans were more likely Turkic nomads, and their roaming spread the symbol. If you're interested, the Vedas and other Hindu texts had their predecessors written during this time, when the Aryan people yeeted their way into Indus society and found their way into the priestly and upper-classes over a period of hundreds of years of integration, according to my understanding. I'm sure LP or someone more versed on history could correct me if I'm wrong.

/skip
